        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 1:56PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 156 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Caddo Valley, or 8 miles north of Arkadelphia, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Arkadelphia...                    Malvern...
Caddo Valley...                   Perla...
Donaldson...                      Friendship...
Lono...                           Lower Lake Recreation Area...
Social Hill...                    Joan...
De Roche...                       Willow...
Midway in Hot Spring County...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
